coordinates, but are the row/column of the tile at the current zoom level. <a href="http://www.robblackwell.org.uk/">Rob
Blackwell </a>has earlier <a href="http://viavirtualearth.com/VVE/Articles/RollYourOwnTileServer.ashx">posted
an article </a>on how to convert these to longitude/latitude values. 
</p>
