";s:8:"body_p_a";s:7:"Umbraco";s:15:"body_p_strong_u";s:22:"variables are constant";s:5:"title";s:18:"Constant variables";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://www.sharpgis.net/PermaLink,guid,341c81bf-0c52-4994-9d65-ce162f1c0f49.aspx";s:4:"link";s:57:"http://www.sharpgis.net/2006/07/06/ConstantVariables.aspx";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Thu, 06 Jul 2006 14:50:01 GMT";s:11:"description";s:694:"<p>
I've had the pleasure of working a lot with XSLT the last couple of weeks while implementing
a site in <a href="http://www.umbraco.org">Umbraco</a>. Developing macros in XSLT
is somewhat far from what I've been&nbsp;used to in other higher-level languages I've
worked with.
</p>
<p>
The last couple of days I've been struggling a lot with the scope of variables as
well as updating some variables in a loop, without much luck. It now turns out that
this is not possible because "<strong><u>variables are constant</u></strong>" in XSLT.
I wonder who came up with that idea...
</p>
